                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>1999-12-29</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>The book is a must-read for any community considering investing in a private, for-profit sports facility. Nevertheless, it provides a less than comprehensive perspective. I would recommend reading the book along with  Minor League Baseball and Local Economic Development for a wider view of  what communities might encounter when making this major, and occassionally  unnecessary, investment.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Whose money is it anyway?</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
